---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const faq = [
  { q: 'Can you turn into a bat in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Yes. As a vampire you can shapeshift into a bat, which is a quick way to get around the town at night — flying around is described as conveniently fast.' },
  { q: 'What other forms can you shapeshift into?', a: 'The developers have hinted that you can learn to shapeshift into other forms beyond the bat, and demo players have described dashing around as a cat. The full list of forms is expected at launch.' },
  { q: 'How do you unlock shapeshifting?', a: 'Shapeshifting is part of your vampire lineage and supernatural abilities. Exactly how and when each form unlocks will be confirmed when the full game launches on ' + GAME.releaseLabel + '.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Shapeshifting', item: new URL('/shapeshifting', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Shapeshifting — Bat Form & Other Forms"
  description="How shapeshifting works in Moonlight Peaks: turning into a bat to travel at night, the other forms devs have hinted at, and how it fits your vampire powers."
  path="/shapeshifting"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Shapeshifting' }]}
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Shapeshifting</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>shapeshifting</em></h1>
      <p class="intro">
        One of the perks of being a vampire in {GAME.title} is changing your shape. Here's what's
        actually confirmed about shapeshifting — and what the developers have only hinted at so far.
        Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Turn into a bat to get around</h2>
      <p>
        The confirmed headline form is the classic vampire bat. Shifting into a bat lets you fly
        around the town quickly at night, which is handy when you're juggling the farm, errands and
        socialising before sunrise.
      </p>

      <h2>Other forms are hinted at</h2>
      <p>
        The studio has teased that you can learn to shapeshift into other forms too, beyond the bat.
        Players who tried the demo described dashing around as a cat, but the complete set of forms —
        and what each one is good for — hasn't been fully detailed yet.
      </p>

      <h2>Part of your vampire powers</h2>
      <p>
        Shapeshifting sits alongside the rest of your supernatural abilities and helps you explore
        everything the town has to offer. It pairs naturally with <a href="/magic">witchcraft and
        potions</a> — and like everything else in your (un-)life, it works around the rule that you
        return to your coffin before the sun comes up.
      </p>

      <h2>Coming at launch ({GAME.releaseLabel})</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The full <strong>list of forms</strong> you can take, beyond the bat.</li>
        <li>How each form <strong>unlocks</strong> and what it's useful for.</li>
        <li>Any limits — energy, timing, or where you can and can't transform.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Pre-launch entry — the full form list lands at launch. Related:
        <a href="/magic">magic & potions</a>, <a href="/character-creator">character creator</a>,
        <a href="/beginner-guide">beginner guide</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
